Lift 6 GHz EIRP cap to LPI (Low Power Indoor) limits.

The upstream wireless-regdb uses a conservative 12 dBm cap for the US 6 GHz
entry and 14 dBm for HK. These figures are well below what FCC and HKCA 1081
allow for indoor LPI operation. With the 12/14 dBm cap, real-world WiFi 7
6 GHz throughput collapses on any non-trivial distance.

FCC LPI (47 CFR 15.407) permits 5 dBm/MHz PSD for indoor APs. Per channel
width that translates to:
  80 MHz:  24 dBm EIRP
  160 MHz: 27 dBm EIRP
  320 MHz: 30 dBm EIRP

HKCA 1081 permits 24 dBm EIRP indoor LPI in 5925-6425 MHz.

cfg80211 enforces the regdb value as a ceiling. We set the ceiling to the
FCC max (30 dBm), then UCI 'option txpower' caps per channel width.

Signed-off-by: mingfai <ma@mingf.ai>
---
--- a/db.txt
+++ b/db.txt
@@ -872,7 +872,8 @@ country HK: DFS-ETSI
 	(5250 - 5350 @ 80), (23), DFS, AUTO-BW, NO-OUTDOOR
 	(5470 - 5730 @ 160), (27), DFS
 	(5730 - 5850 @ 80), (36)
-	(5925 - 6425 @ 160), (14)
+	# HKCA 1081: 24 dBm EIRP LPI indoor
+	(5925 - 6425 @ 160), (24), NO-OUTDOOR

 # Source:
 # https://www.conatel.gob.hn/doc/Regulacion/resoluciones/2023/NR05-23.pdf
@@ -2052,7 +2053,8 @@ country US: DFS-FCC
 	(5850 - 5895 @ 40), (27), NO-OUTDOOR, AUTO-BW, NO-IR
 	# 6g band
 	# https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2020/05/26/2020-11236/unlicensed-use-of-the-6ghz-band
-	(5925 - 7125 @ 320), (12), NO-OUTDOOR, wmmrule=ETSI
+	# FCC LPI: 5 dBm/MHz PSD; cap = 30 dBm @ 320 MHz, set UCI txpower per BW
+	(5925 - 7125 @ 320), (30), NO-OUTDOOR, wmmrule=ETSI
 	# 60g band
 	# reference: section IV-D https://docs.fcc.gov/public/attachments/FCC-16-89A1.pdf
 	# channels 1-6 EIRP=40dBm(43dBm peak)
